The paper deals with crowd behavior understanding using video sequences, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training emotion-based classifiers, which is a machine learning approach (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the dataset used for the experiments, which is related to data mining and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of emotions in crowd behavior understanding also has implications for human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves analyzing and processing video data, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
